Northern Youths have organized to mobilise support for the presidential candidate of the Peoples Democratic party (PDP), former Vice President Atiku Abubakar for the 2023 elections.
The Youths under the aegis of Northern Youths Media Influencers declared to mobilise extensively for the victory of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) and Atiku Abubakar, the candidate, in the 2023 presidential and other elections.
The Northern Youths at a solidarity rally for Atiku in Kano State, declared that they decided to support Atiku’s presidential candidacy because of his track records and keen interest in programmes designed to develop the youths of the country.
The youths were assembled from the 44 Local Government Areas of Kano State for the solidarity rally for Atiku.
The Special Adviser to Atiku Abubakar on Youth Affairs, Aliyu Abass, at the rally stated that former Vice President Atiku is the best man for the job of Nigeria’s next President. Abass noted that the PDP presidential candidate is very friendly and accommodating of youths, pointing out that he is the unifier Nigeria currently needs.
At the rally, the new executives of the Social Media influencers for Atiku Abubakar presidential campaign was inaugurated.
